The Senate has confirmed the appointment of the nominees of National Commissioners in accordance with the relevant provisions of the constitution. The Committee on the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) had submitted the report on confirmation of the appointment of the National Commissioners. The Committee Chairman, Senator Kabiru Gaya, in his report explained that the nominees were all invited and asked questions on their part which was quite satisfactory adding that most of the nominees are accomplished Nigerians who have contributed to the national economy in their various fields of endeavors. Euro Surges As Record Inflation Adds Pressure On ECB Casualties confirmed As Turkey Targets PKK In Iraq, Syria The Deputy Senate President, Ovie Omo-Agege however commended the committee for their due diligence. He said: “That the Senate do receive and consider the report of the Committee on the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on the confirmation of the nominations of the following persons for appointment as National Commissioner for the Independent National Electoral Commission.” According to him, the election was a serious exercise in Nigeria to be left in hands of competent and serious-minded citizens which President Muhammadu Buhari eventually forwarded to the Senate. The Senate President, Dr. Ahmad Ibrahim Lawan however called for confirmation of the nominees. The confirmed nominees are: POLL 1. Malami Mohammed Haruna (Niger) – National Commissioner2. Mrs. May Agbamuche-Mbu (Delta) – National Commissioner3. Ukeagu Kenneth Nnamdi (Abia) – National Commissioner4. Maj. Gen. A.B.Alkali (rtd) (Adamawa) – National Commissioner5. Engr. (Prof.) Rhoda H. Gumus (Bayelsa) – National Commissioner6. Mr Sam Olumekun (Ondo) – National Commissioner7. Olaniyi Olaleye (Ondo) – Resident Electoral Commissioner